<sn><md>## Earthquake{.text-center .fg-red}

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
&gt; An earthquake is a `sudden shaking or vibration` of the Earth’s surface caused by the `movement of rocks` deep inside the Earth’s crust.

It occurs when ==energy stored in the Earth’s lithosphere is suddenly released==, producing ++seismic waves++. Earthquakes are one of the most powerful natural hazards, capable of causing massive destruction to life, property, and the environment.
:::

